WGC BARBADOS WORLD CUP
December 7, 2006
Angel Cabrera
Andres Romero
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   


  Q. Same name, Romero but much  younger, good partner, first time you have not played with Eduardo; is that  right?   
 ANGEL CABRERA: I played with Gonzalez last year and  1998. He's a good boy.   
  
  Q.  A lot of talent and golf potential?   
 ANGEL CABRERA: Absolutely.   
  
  Q.  What about today then? You made a  lot of birdies on the back nine?   
 ANGEL CABRERA: We didn't play well the first nine holes and  thank goodness he played well on the back nine holes. And then on the other back nine I played, and  we combined.   
  
  Q.  Who was making all the birdies?   
 ANGEL CABRERA: I made four birdies.   
  
  Q.  That's good, in this weather. So  I remember the first World Cup, you were so close to winning with Eduardo, is  this a big ambition to win?   
 ANGEL CABRERA: Yes, always, always. It's one objective that I have not achieved  in my career and I want to finish it in this tournament.   
  
  Q.  And I see, just like Bernhard Langer, this is your son?   
 ANGEL CABRERA: Yes, this is Angel.   
  
  Q.  How old is he?   
 ANGEL CABRERA: 15.   
  
  Q.  What does your other son, Federico, play off?  
 ANGEL CABRERA: Zero.   
  
  Q.  It's nice to have the calmly with you?   
 ANGEL CABRERA: Yes, very good, especially in this  tournament.   
  
  Q.  And Andres, did you enjoy your experience?   
 ANDRES ROMERO: The first hole we made a bogey from 110  yards. But luckily Angel made a birdie  on the second hole, and in the end it was like, wow. Now I'm more quiet, relaxed. In the end I started to feel good.   
  
  Q.  Can you see why Angel is such a good player and won so many titles?   
 ANDRES ROMERO: He's a very recognised player and he showed  it in the back nine. Well, he made three  birdies in a row and then he made a birdie.  Well, that was very important for him to have confidence in his game.  
   
